	bool "Use Gale formally verified fatal"
	help
	  Use Gale formally verified fatal error classification for
	  kernel/fatal.c. Recovery action determination based on error
	  reason and context is handled by verified Rust code. IRQ lock,
	  coredump, thread abort, and halt remain native Zephyr C.
	  Requires a Rust toolchain for the target architecture.

config GALE_KERNEL_MEMPOOL
	bool "Use Gale formally verified mempool"
	help
	  Use Gale formally verified fixed-block pool allocation tracking.
	  Block count increment/decrement with bounds checking are handled
	  by verified Rust code. Bitarray management, alignment, and actual
	  memory allocation remain native Zephyr C.
	  Requires a Rust toolchain for the target architecture.

