	  by verified Rust code. Bitarray management, stack allocation,
	  and thread creation remain native Zephyr C.
	  Requires a Rust toolchain for the target architecture.

config GALE_KERNEL_SMP_STATE
	bool "Use Gale formally verified SMP state"
	depends on SMP
	help
	  Use Gale formally verified SMP CPU state tracking for
	  kernel/smp.c. CPU start/stop count tracking is handled by
	  verified Rust code. IPI signaling, interrupt stack setup,
	  and arch CPU start remain native Zephyr C.
	  Requires a Rust toolchain for the target architecture.

config GALE_KERNEL_SCHED
	bool "Use Gale formally verified scheduler"
	depends on MULTITHREADING
	help
	  Use Gale formally verified scheduler primitives for
	  kernel/sched.c. next_up thread selection and preemption
	  decision logic are handled by verified Rust code. Run queue
	  data structures, thread state transitions, wait queues, and
	  SMP IPI remain native Zephyr C.
	  Requires a Rust toolchain for the target architecture.
